   <conbody>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <hazardstatement conref="../../Library/Warnings_Library_0000325173.dita#war_lib/before_maint_check"
                             class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
               <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                  <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
                  <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
               </messagepanel>
               <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                  <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard "/>
                  <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid "/>
               </messagepanel>
            </hazardstatement>
            <hazardstatement type="note" class="+ topic/note hazard-d/hazardstatement ">
               <messagepanel class="+ topic/ul hazard-d/messagepanel ">
                  <typeofhazard class="+ topic/li hazard-d/typeofhazard ">loss of output voltage</typeofhazard>
                  <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">If the system is turned off without the external manual
bypass in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> the output voltage is lost.</howtoavoid>
                  <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">When the external manual bypass switch is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Bypass</b> position, it is not possible for the system to automatically switch
back to inverter operation in case the bypass mains becomes unavailable.</howtoavoid>
                  <howtoavoid class="+ topic/li hazard-d/howtoavoid ">Always coordinate maintenance and turning off or on the
system with the users of the consumers. Make sure that users of the
connected consumers are informed before proceeding.</howtoavoid>
               </messagepanel>
            </hazardstatement>
            <p class="- topic/p ">Make the following checks annually:</p>
            <ol class="- topic/ol ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Perform both the <xref href="../Monthly_Check_CPT_0000327541.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/> and <xref href="../Semi-Annual_Check_CPT_0000327540.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Isolate <ph platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/ph ">the system/unit with the manual
bypass switch or turn it off</ph>
                     <ph platform="SDC" class="- topic/ph ">and turn off the
system/unit</ph>, see the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Operating Manual</i> for more information.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If the system is dusty, clean the system from dust with a vacuum
cleaner.<note class="- topic/note "> Do not use any liquid to clean!</note>
                  </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">If applicable, check and follow any annual maintenance recommendations
by other original equipment manufacturer (OEM).</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Re-install any removed protection covers.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Turn on the system or unit, see the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Operating Manual</i> for more information.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Perform a functional check of the system to verify that the
system switches correctly between operating modes (according to operation
mode priority). See chapter <xref href="1220236_Function_Check_of_a_Unit_CPT_DD00545785.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="PxW WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Perform a function check of the ISBS solution
to check that the ISBS takes over if the controller board is inoperable.
See chapter <xref href="1220236_Function_Check_of_the_ISBS_Solution_CPT_DD00545784.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
            </ol>
         </sectiondiv>
